la, suggest that we are entering a new phase in human evolutionary history—one that makes the future less predictable and more interesting than ever before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEvolution (Biology). 0aHuman beings. 0aHuman evolution. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030020871940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022450440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224504423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300224504/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY